      "message": "Patch Set 1: I would prefer that you didn't submit this\n\nIt is actually a benefit that multiple log files are not dumped in the same second. If there are multiple threads racing to dump the debug log at the same time then the later logs will not contain any useful information, and just fill up /tmp.  Even if the same thread is dumping a log repeatedly the later logs will not contain any new useful information. \n\nIf anything, the console error should just be quieted to avoid annoying the administrator c",
